The official reason for the HTTP status code 410 is "Gone". This status code indicates that the requested resource is no longer available and will not be available again. It is typically used when a resource has been permanently removed or relocated. For example, if a website has been shut down or a file has been deleted, a 410 status code may be returned. This status code is different from a 404 status code, which indicates that the requested resource was not found but may still be available in the future.

It's important to note that the information provided by the HTTPStatus tool in this case seems to be incorrect as it shows "Unknown" for both reason and category. The correct reason for 410 is "Gone".

